aas:langStringTextType.aas:text: Aspect to indicate if there is a return request for a product.
Entity encapsulating the conditions the product is in.
Entity for common measurements of an item (mass, count, linear, area, volume, misc) with an unit and a value.
Specifies the time period when the need exists
Entity defining a range of dates to define a time period.
Entity encapsulating different unique identifier of the product (manufacturingPartID, OeNumber and/or serialNumber)
A local identifier enables identification of a part in a specific dataspace, but is not unique in Catena-X dataspace. Multiple local identifiers may exist.
A list of key value pairs for local identifiers, which are composed of a key and a corresponding value.
Entity of an address. Model follows specification of BPDM (Business Partner Data Management).
Entity for a thoroughfare which consists of a type, value and number.
Entity for a locality which consists of a key and a value.
Entity for a premise which consists of a type (technical key) and a value.
Entity for a postal delivery point which consists of a technical key and a value.
Entity for a postcode which consists of a type plus a value.
Property describing the classification of a part.
Encapsulates data related to the classification of the part.
Aspect to indicate if there is a return request for a product.

aas:langStringDefinitionTypeIec61360.aas:text: Aspect to indicate if there is a return request for a product.
Describes the fact whether a vehicle, assembly or part needs to be returned to requestor.
Describes WHY a vehicle, assembly or part needs to be returned to the requestor and under which conditions.
Describes date when the return request was placed.
Describes until when the return request is valid.
Completeness of the product, e.g. missing parts are not acceptable.
Information on whether the product has been dismantled.
Information on mechanical damage to the part, e.g. two broken ribs or part deformation indicate mechanical damage.
Information on whether the product has corrosion.
Information on whether the product has been discoloured.
Current mileage of the component
textual description of the product conditions
The description of the product within the marketplace that might differ from the digital twin.
The quantity value associated with the unit.
The unit of an item. Common units may be related to mass, count, linear, area, volume or misc.
The desired quantity of the on the marketplace offered product in SKU.
The first day of the period
The last day of the period.
Specifies the time period when the need exists
Depicts if the manufacturer issued a recall (e.g. for security reasons). In conjunction with property needsReturn it can be expressed if the item has to be returned or can directly be destroyed.
The key of a local identifier.
The value of an identifier.
A local identifier enables identification of a part in a specific dataspace, but is not unique in Catena-X dataspace. Multiple local identifiers may exist.

Part ID as assigned by the manufacturer of the part. The Part ID identifies the part (as designed)in the manufacturer`s dataspace. The Part ID does not reference a specific instance of a part and thus should not be confused with the serial number.

Part ID as assigned by the manufacturer of the part. The Part ID identifies the part (as designed)in the customer`s dataspace. The Part ID does not reference a specific instance of a part and thus should not be confused with the serial number.
The unique identifier of the product (via manufacturingPartID, OeNumber and/or serialNumber)
Technical key of a thoroughfare. As specified by BPDM, this can be a "STREET" or a different type.
Value of a thoroughfare, e.g. name of a street.
Number of a thoroughfare. As used differently in international context, this number can contain both numerical and alphanumerical values.
Street or thorough road name.
Technical key of a locality.
Value of a locality, e.g. name of a city ("Mannheim").
Locality belonging to an address.
Technical key of a premise.
Value of a premise, e.g. name or designation of a particular site.
Premise of an address, e.g. a specific "BUILDING" but can also be used for naming a particular site.
Technical key of a postal delivery point.
Value of a postal delivery point, e.g. designation of a gate.
Delivery point, e.g. designation of a gate.
The short variation of the name of the country.
Country of an address.
The value of a post code.
The technical key of a post code.
Postal code of the address.
The address that the product should be delivered to
Information, in which countries/areas the component has been in use
Until when should the product arrive (if known)
Timestamp of the manufacturing date as the final step in production process (e.g. final quality check, ready-for-shipment event)
Name of the part as assigned by the customer
Identified classification standards that align to the Catena-X needs.
The classification ID of the part type according to the corresponding standard definition mentioned in the key value pair.
Optional property describing the classification standard.
Property describing the classification of a part.
